        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 1 at 7:46PM CDT until May 1 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 746 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 14 miles northwest
of Adrian, or 18 miles southeast of Nara Visa, moving southeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.

This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
western Oldham County.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
